verses.text_plain: Now the sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel, (for he was the firstborn; but, forasmuch as he defiled his father’s bed, his birthright was given unto the sons of Joseph the son of Israel: and the genealogy is not to be reckoned after the birthright.
verses.verse_html: 1Now the sons of Reuben the firstborn of Israel, (for he was the firstborn; but, forasmuch as he defiled his father’s bed, his birthright was given unto the sons of Joseph the son of Israel: and the genealogy is not to be reckoned after the birthright.

tokens.text: and the genealogy is not to be reckoned

verses.text_plain: For Judah prevailed above his brethren, and of him came the chief ruler; but the birthright was Joseph’s:)
verses.verse_html:
2For Judah prevailed above his brethren, and of him came the chief ruler; but the birthright was Joseph’s:) ▼
▼ chief…: or, prince

verses.text_plain: The sons, I say, of Reuben the firstborn of Israel were, Hanoch, and Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi.
verses.verse_html: 3The sons, I say, of Reuben the firstborn of Israel were, Hanoch, and Pallu, Hezron, and Carmi.

verses.text_plain: The sons of Joel; Shemaiah his son, Gog his son, Shimei his son,
verses.verse_html: 4The sons of Joel; Shemaiah his son, Gog his son, Shimei his son,

verses.text_plain: Micah his son, Reaia his son, Baal his son,
verses.verse_html: 5Micah his son, Reaia his son, Baal his son,

verses.text_plain: Beerah his son, whom Tilgath–pilneser king of Assyria carried away captive: he was prince of the Reubenites.
verses.verse_html:
6Beerah his son, whom Tilgath–pilneser king of Assyria carried away captive: he was prince of the Reubenites. ▼
▼ Tilgath–pilneser: also called, Tiglath–pileser

verses.text_plain: And his brethren by their families, when the genealogy of their generations was reckoned, were the chief, Jeiel, and Zechariah,
verses.verse_html: 7And his brethren by their families, when the genealogy of their generations was reckoned, were the chief, Jeiel, and Zechariah,

verses.text_plain: And Bela the son of Azaz, the son of Shema, the son of Joel, who dwelt in Aroer, even unto Nebo and Baal–meon:
verses.verse_html:
8And Bela the son of Azaz, the son of Shema, the son of Joel, who dwelt in Aroer, even unto Nebo and Baal–meon: ▼
▼ Shema: or, Shemaiah

verses.text_plain: And eastward he inhabited unto the entering in of the wilderness from the river Euphrates: because their cattle were multiplied in the land of Gilead.
verses.verse_html: 9And eastward he inhabited unto the entering in of the wilderness from the river Euphrates: because their cattle were multiplied in the land of Gilead.

verses.text_plain: And in the days of Saul they made war with the Hagarites, who fell by their hand: and they dwelt in their tents throughout all the east land of Gilead.
verses.verse_html:
10And in the days of Saul they made war with the Hagarites, who fell by their hand: and they dwelt in their tents throughout all the east land of Gilead. ▼
▼ throughout…: Heb. upon all the face of the east

footnotes.body_text: ▼ throughout…: Heb. upon all the face of the east
footnotes.body_html: ▼ throughout…: Heb. upon all the face of the east

verses.text_plain: And the children of Gad dwelt over against them, in the land of Bashan unto Salchah:
verses.verse_html: 11And the children of Gad dwelt over against them, in the land of Bashan unto Salchah:

tokens.text: over against them, in the land

verses.text_plain: Joel the chief, and Shapham the next, and Jaanai, and Shaphat in Bashan.
verses.verse_html: 12Joel the chief, and Shapham the next, and Jaanai, and Shaphat in Bashan.

verses.text_plain: And their brethren of the house of their fathers were, Michael, and Meshullam, and Sheba, and Jorai, and Jachan, and Zia, and Heber, seven.
verses.verse_html: 13And their brethren of the house of their fathers were, Michael, and Meshullam, and Sheba, and Jorai, and Jachan, and Zia, and Heber, seven.

verses.text_plain: These are the children of Abihail the son of Huri, the son of Jaroah, the son of Gilead, the son of Michael, the son of Jeshishai, the son of Jahdo, the son of Buz;
verses.verse_html: 14These are the children of Abihail the son of Huri, the son of Jaroah, the son of Gilead, the son of Michael, the son of Jeshishai, the son of Jahdo, the son of Buz;

verses.text_plain: Ahi the son of Abdiel, the son of Guni, chief of the house of their fathers.
verses.verse_html: 15Ahi the son of Abdiel, the son of Guni, chief of the house of their fathers.

verses.text_plain: And they dwelt in Gilead in Bashan, and in her towns, and in all the suburbs of Sharon, upon their borders.
verses.verse_html:
16And they dwelt in Gilead in Bashan, and in her towns, and in all the suburbs of Sharon, upon their borders. ▼
▼ their…: Heb. their goings forth

footnotes.body_html: ▼ their…: Heb. their goings forth

verses.text_plain: All these were reckoned by genealogies in the days of Jotham king of Judah, and in the days of Jeroboam king of Israel.
verses.verse_html: 17All these were reckoned by genealogies in the days of Jotham king of Judah, and in the days of Jeroboam king of Israel.

tokens.text: All these were reckoned by genealogies

verses.text_plain: The sons of Reuben, and the Gadites, and half the tribe of Manasseh, of valiant men, men able to bear buckler and sword, and to shoot with bow, and skilful in war, were four and forty thousand seven hundred and threescore, that went out to the war.
verses.verse_html:
18The sons of Reuben, and the Gadites, and half the tribe of Manasseh, of valiant men, men able to bear buckler and sword, and to shoot with bow, and skilful in war, were four and forty thousand seven hundred and threescore, that went out to the war. ▼
▼ valiant…: Heb. sons of valour

footnotes.body_html: ▼ valiant…: Heb. sons of valour

verses.text_plain: And they made war with the Hagarites, with Jetur, and Nephish, and Nodab.
verses.verse_html: 19And they made war with the Hagarites, with Jetur, and Nephish, and Nodab.

verses.text_plain: And they were helped against them, and the Hagarites were delivered into their hand, and all that were with them: for they cried to God in the battle, and he was intreated of them; because they put their trust in him.
verses.verse_html: 20And they were helped against them, and the Hagarites were delivered into their hand, and all that were with them: for they cried to God in the battle, and he was intreated of them; because they put their trust in him.

tokens.text: of them; because they put their trust

verses.text_plain: And they took away their cattle; of their camels fifty thousand, and of sheep two hundred and fifty thousand, and of asses two thousand, and of men an hundred thousand.
verses.verse_html:
21And they took away their cattle; of their camels fifty thousand, and of sheep two hundred and fifty thousand, and of asses two thousand, and of men an hundred thousand. ▼
▼ took…: Heb. led captive
 , ▼
▼ men: Heb. souls of men

footnotes.body_html: ▼ took…: Heb. led captive
▼ men: Heb. souls of men

verses.text_plain: For there fell down many slain, because the war was of God. And they dwelt in their steads until the captivity.
verses.verse_html: 22For there fell down many slain, because the war was of God. And they dwelt in their steads until the captivity.

tokens.text: in their steads until the captivity

verses.text_plain: And the children of the half tribe of Manasseh dwelt in the land: they increased from Bashan unto Baal–hermon and Senir, and unto mount Hermon.
verses.verse_html: 23And the children of the half tribe of Manasseh dwelt in the land: they increased from Bashan unto Baal–hermon and Senir, and unto mount Hermon.

verses.text_plain: And these were the heads of the house of their fathers, even Epher, and Ishi, and Eliel, and Azriel, and Jeremiah, and Hodaviah, and Jahdiel, mighty men of valour, famous men, and heads of the house of their fathers.
verses.verse_html:
24And these were the heads of the house of their fathers, even Epher, and Ishi, and Eliel, and Azriel, and Jeremiah, and Hodaviah, and Jahdiel, mighty men of valour, famous men, and heads of the house of their fathers. ▼
▼ famous…: Heb. men of names

footnotes.body_html: ▼ famous…: Heb. men of names

verses.text_plain: And they transgressed against the God of their fathers, and went a whoring after the gods of the people of the land, whom God destroyed before them.
verses.verse_html: 25And they transgressed against the God of their fathers, and went a whoring after the gods of the people of the land, whom God destroyed before them.

verses.text_plain: And the God of Israel stirred up the spirit of Pul king of Assyria, and the spirit of Tilgath–pilneser king of Assyria, and he carried them away, even the Reubenites, and the Gadites, and the half tribe of Manasseh, and brought them unto Halah, and Habor, and Hara, and to the river Gozan, unto this day.
verses.verse_html: 26And the God of Israel stirred up the spirit of Pul king of Assyria, and the spirit of Tilgath–pilneser king of Assyria, and he carried them away, even the Reubenites, and the Gadites, and the half tribe of Manasseh, and brought them unto Halah, and Habor, and Hara, and to the river Gozan, unto this day.
